<font color="#FF0000">EMOTIONLESS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Oct 26 11:35:15 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
    It was a long time ago, and i thought I'd put most of my emotions about the war behind me.  Well, it not that, I'd at least had them under control.<br>
 <br>
   Last week, after dinner with old friends, as was our custom, we went to our friends house for coffee, desert and conversaion. <br><br>
  Both of the other couples were career soldiers and Viet Nam vets. <br><br>
   For what ever reason, the conversation came around to Viet-Nam.  Beleive it or not, that's not ususal.  In the course of the conversation, one of the wifes said that the Vietnamese really didn't like us and really didn't beleive in the war.  They were just dupes<br><br>
   I gave a couple of examples of the Vietnamese I'd known and before I knew it was shouting at the poor women.  <br><br>
   Long silence and change of subject followed.<br><br>
   My wife was embarrased and critiqued my performance and the only excuse I could come up with was &quot;she pissed me off.&quot; <br>
    Hell of a thing to happen to a 64 year old man over a war over twenty years gone.<br><br>
   So much for logic and controlled emotions.<br><br>
   It's hell being Italin AND Irish.<br><br>
Andy
